tab2.text1:
<TextStyle.Red> #1. Dont be a Dick!!</>
 <TextStyle.Green>#2. No Griefing or Trolling:</> Avoid actions that negatively impact the experience of other players, such as leading dangerous creatures to their bases or intentionally causing harm to their tames or structures.
 <TextStyle.Green>#3. Respect Taming and Building Rules:</> Be considerate of other survivors by not blocking critical resources, spawn points, or taming areas. Do not build excessively large or obstructive structures. And dont leave taming pens everywhere.
 <TextStyle.Green>#4. Report Bugs and Exploits:</> If you discover a game-breaking bug or exploit, report it to the server administrators rather than taking advantage of it. Exploiting game mechanics is not allowed.
 <TextStyle.Green>#5. Be a Helpful and Supportive Community Member:</> Assist new players, share knowledge, and be a positive presence on the server. Building a friendly and cooperative community is essential for a successful PvE experience.
 <TextStyle.Green>#6. No Blocking Obelisks and Artifacts:</> Do not build near or block access to obelisks, artifact caves, or other crucial map locations, as these are important for progression.
 <TextStyle.Green>#7. No Cave Blocking:</> Do not obstruct access to caves, as these locations are vital for players to explore and gather resources.
 <TextStyle.Green>#8. Follow Admin Guidelines:</> Respect the server administrators and moderators. They have the authority to enforce rules, resolve disputes, and maintain order on the server.
 <TextStyle.Green>#9. Report Rule Violations:</> If you witness someone breaking these rules, report it to the server administrators or moderators. Do not take matters into your own hands.

 <TextStyle.Green>These rules are designed to foster a cooperative and enjoyable PvE environment for all players on the server. The Server Admin will typically enforce these rules to ensure a positive gaming experience for everyone.</>
